<item>
            <title>[LU-10218] errors not propagated to changelog readers</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10218</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Reviewing &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/29818/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/29818/&lt;/a&gt; I noticed that errors are not being propagated to changelog readers. I suggest that crs_err be changed to int and the errno associated to any errors encountered be stored there. Then this value can be used in chlg_read() if no records were emitted. Also the return value of chld_load() will also be the return value of kthread_stop() in chlg_release(). clhg_release() should save and return any errors there too.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
